## ScrollArea Component

The `ScrollArea` component provides a customizable and accessible scrollable container. It's built on top of Radix UI's ScrollArea primitive, offering enhanced styling and theming capabilities.

### Key Exports

*   **`ScrollArea`**: The main component for creating scrollable areas. It accepts children and can be configured with various props.
*   **`ScrollBar`**: A component for rendering the scrollbar within the `ScrollArea`. It can be oriented vertically or horizontally.

### Props

**`ScrollArea` Props:**

*   `className`: Custom CSS class names to apply to the scroll area container.
*   `children`: The content to be displayed within the scrollable area.
*   `...props`: All other standard `ScrollAreaPrimitive.Root` props are supported.

**`ScrollBar` Props:**

*   `className`: Custom CSS class names to apply to the scrollbar.
*   `orientation`: ('vertical' | 'horizontal') Specifies the orientation of the scrollbar. Defaults to 'vertical'.
*   `...props`: All other standard `ScrollAreaPrimitive.ScrollAreaScrollbar` props are supported.

### Usage Example

```tsx
import { ScrollArea } from '@/components/ui/scroll-area';

function MyScrollableComponent() {
  return (
    <ScrollArea className="h-[200px] w-[350px] rounded-md border">
      <div className="p-4">
        <h4 className="mb-4 text-sm font-medium leading-none">Tags</h4>
        {Array.from({ length: 10 }).map((_, i, arr) => (
          <div
            key={i}
            className="text-sm"
          >
            Tag {i + 1}
            {i < arr.length - 1 && <br />}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </ScrollArea>
  );
}

export default MyScrollableComponent;
```

This example demonstrates how to use the `ScrollArea` component to create a scrollable container with a fixed height and width, containing a list of items. The `ScrollBar` component is automatically included and managed by the `ScrollArea` component.
